Setting up Edge device on Pi Zero 2W


Phase 0: Notion Backend Setup
You need to create a "digital brain" for your Array Button to talk to.
Step 1: Create the "Bot" (Integration)
	1	Go to Notion My Integrations in your browser.
	2	Click + New integration.
	3	Name: Array Button.
	4	Associated Workspace: Select your main workspace.
	5	Type: Internal Integration.
	6	Click Submit.
	7	⚠️ COPY THE SECRET: You will see a long code starting with secret_....
	◦	Save this! This is your NOTION_TOKEN.
Step 2: Create the Inventory Database
	1	Open Notion and create a new Page.
	2	Type /database and select Database - Inline.
	3	Name it "Site Inventory".
	4	Setup the Columns (Properties):
	◦	Column 1 (Name): Rename to Item Name. (Type: Title)
	◦	Column 2: Rename to quantity used. (Type: Number) -> Crucial: Must be lowercase 'q' if that's what the code expects, but typically Notion defaults to Title Case. The script uses "quantity used", so name it exactly that.
	◦	Column 3: Rename to Person. (Type: Person)
	◦	Optional: Add a "Date" column (Type: Created time) to auto-log when it happened.
	5	Pre-fill the Items:
	◦	Add rows for: Cement, Bricks, Steel, Sand, Water.
	◦	Note: The script looks for exact text matches, so ensure these exist.
Step 3: Give the Bot Permission
	1	Go to your new "Site Inventory" database page.
	2	Click the Three Dots (...) at the top right of the page.
	3	Scroll down to Connect to (or "Add connections").
	4	Search for "Array Button" (the integration you created in Step 1).
	5	Click it and confirm.
	◦	If you don't do this, the Pi will get a "404 Not Found" error.
Step 4: Get the Database ID
	1	Click the Share button (top right) -> Copy link.
	2	Paste the link into a notepad. It will look like this: https://www.notion.so/username/819b3a3d87244fe9820fae78679602d4?v=...
	3	Extract the ID: It is the 32-character code between the slash / and the question mark ?.
	◦	Example ID: 819b3a3d87244fe9820fae78679602d4
	◦	Save this! This is your DATABASE_ID.


